Sentencas: BaCe0.7Sn0.1Gd0.2O3-sigma (BCSG) and BaCe0.8 Gd0.2O3-sigma (BCG) powders were prepared by solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: A stable and easily sintering BaCe0.7Sn0.1Gd0.2O3-δ electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After exposure in 5% CO2+5% H2O+ 90% N-2 at 500 degrees C for 5 h, the BCSG powders were hardly affected while the BCG powders decomposed into CeO2 and BaCO3 phases.
Titulo: A stable and easily sintering BaCe0.7Sn0.1Gd0.2O3-δ electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the relative density of BCSG reaches 97%, while the BCG just displays 91% after sintering at 1,400 degrees C. The BCSG displays a conductivity of 0.01 S/cm at 700 degrees C in humid hydrogen, which is quite close to 0.012 S/cm for BCG.
Titulo: A stable and easily sintering BaCe0.7Sn0.1Gd0.2O3-δ electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A fuel cell with BCSG exhibits 1.02 V for open circuit voltage, 420 mW/cm(2) for peak performance and 0.23 Omega cm(2) for interfacial resistance at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A stable and easily sintering BaCe0.7Sn0.1Gd0.2O3-δ electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells
